  "music": "or &#39;Nun ruhen alle Wälder&#39; or &#39;O Welt, Ich Muss Dich Lassen&#39; Heinrich Isaac, 1490 Johann Sebastian Bach, 1734",
  "tune": "Innsbruck",
  "lyrics": {
    "v1": "Now rest beneath night&#39;s shadow The woodland, field, and meadow, The world in slumber lies; But Thou, my heart, awake thee, To prayer and song betake thee; Let praise to thy Crea- tor rise.",
    "v2": "The radiant sun hath vanished, His golden rays are banished By night, the foe of day; But Christ, the Sun of gladness, Dispelling all my sadness, Within my heart holds constant sway.",
    "v3": "The rule of day is over And shining jewels cover The heaven&#39;s boundless blue. Thus I shall shine in heaven, Where crowns of gold are given To all who faithful prove and true.",
    "v4": "To rest my body hasteth, Aside its garments casteth, Types of mortality; These I put off and ponder How Christ will give me yonder A robe of glorious majesty.",
    "v5": "Lord Jesus, who dost love me, Oh, spread Thy wings above me And shield me from alarm! Though evil would assail me, Thy mercy will not fail me: I rest in Thy protecting arm."
  },
